<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8293569>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. Changes in the profile of volatiles released by all Pinus pinaster trees being fed on by Monochamus galloprovincialis adults. Bars: standard error. Letters in the table on the right side of the graph represent ANOVA post-hoc Fisher's Least Significant Difference test Homogenous Groups; (1) ANOVA with all volatiles: F(16,629) = 4.07; p <0.0001***; (2) ANOVA without α-pinene and β-pinene: F(14,555) = 4.63; p" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8293569/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8293571>
    dc:description "Fig. 2. Changes in the profile of volatiles released by Pinus pinaster trees being fed on by Monochamus galloprovincialis adults, with trees grouped according to their essential oil chemotypes: β-pinene, α-pinene, and δ-3-carene EO dominance (chemotype 1, C1 in dark grey) and δ-3-carene only in trace amounts (chemotype 2, C2 in white). Bars: standard error. Letters in the table on the right side of the graph represent ANOVA post-hoc Fisher's Least Significant Difference test Homogenous Groups; Chemotype 1 (C1): F(16,170) = 1.58; p = 0.078*; Chemotype 2 (C2): F(16,442) = 4.04; p <0.0001***." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8293571/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

